<div class="helpText">
	<h3>To use EBSCO eBooks:</h3>
	<a target='_blank' href='{$path}/files/econtent_help/ebsco.pdf'><img src="{$path}/images/pdficon_small.png" alt="Printable Help"/> Printable Version</a>
	<ol>
		<li>Search the library's catalog for EBSCO eBooks you want to read.</li>
		<li>Click the <b>Access EBook</b> button for the book.</li>
		<li>You will be prompted for your name and library barcode or barcode and password for access to the EBSCO website.</li>
		<li>You will be redirected to the EBSCO site after you are authenticated.</li>
		<li>You will now be able to read the book online by selecting the <b>eBook Full Text</b> link.
		<br /> <em>Note: EBSCO eBooks are available to one person at a time. If the book is in use by another student, you will see the following note: <br/>"Sorry, this eBook is in use". Check back later to gain access. </em>
		</li>
		<li>Portions of the eBook may be printed to PDF by clicking on the <b>Print icon</b> on the right side of the screen.</li>
		<li>You can search within the results by clicking the <b>Search within icon</b> on the right side of the screen.</li>
	</ol>
</div>
